---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Cannabis Lab Testing Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Lab Testing Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to cannabis product testing in Maine. Requirements, compliance, and working with licensed testing laboratories."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581091226825-a6a2a5aee158?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Lab Testing Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Mandatory testing panels and passing/failing protocol</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Testing Checklist</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal Basis</strong></td><td>28-B M.R.S. §503, OCP Rule Chapter 5</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>All Products</strong></td><td>Must test before sale</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Mandatory Panels</strong></td><td>Potency, microbials, pesticides, heavy metals</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Concentrates</strong></td><td>Add: residual solvents</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Cost/Sample</strong></td><td>$50-300</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Testing is Non-Negotiable</h2>
      <p>Maine requires ALL cannabis products to be tested by a licensed lab BEFORE sale. This isn't optional—it's your license to operate.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Testing as Competitive Advantage" type="passion">
      Operators who embrace testing as quality verification build brand trust that competitors cannot match. Your test results are your marketing.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Mandatory Test Panels: 28-B M.R.S. §503</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Product Type</th><th>Required Tests</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Flower</strong></td><td>Potency, microbials, pesticides, heavy metals</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Concentrates</strong></td><td>All above + residual solvents</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Edibles</strong></td><td>Potency, microbials, pesticides, heavy metals</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Topicals</strong></td><td>Potency, microbials (if consumed)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Passing Thresholds</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Contaminant</th><th>Limit</th><th>Consequence of Failure</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>THC potency</strong></td><td>±10% of label</td><td>Relabel or destroy</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Microbial</strong></td><td>As per OCP Chapter 5</td><td>Destroy batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Pesticides</strong></td><td>Various limits</td><td>Destroy batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Heavy Metals</strong></td><td>As per OCP Chapter 5</td><td>Destroy batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Residual Solvents</strong></td><td>5,000 ppm max</td><td>Destroy or re-process</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pro-Hack: The Testing Strategy</h2>
      <p><strong>Optimize your testing workflow:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Batch testing:</strong> Test representative sample, apply to whole batch</li>
        <li><strong>Lab relationships:</strong> Negotiate volume discounts (10-20% off)</li>
        <li><strong>Turnaround time:</strong> Standard is 5-10 days; faster = premium price</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-lab:</strong> Use 2-3 labs to compare results and avoid delays</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Working with Maine Labs</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Consideration</th><th>What to Verify</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>OCP License</td><td>Must be licensed in Maine</td></tr>
          <tr><td>ISO 17025</td><td>Accreditation preferred</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Turnaround</td><td>5-10 days standard</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sample size</td><td>Typically 5-10 units</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cost</td><td>$50-300 per sample</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cost Breakdown</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Test Type</th><th>Cost</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Flower full panel</td><td>$150-250</td><td>Per batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Concentrate panel</td><td>$200-300</td><td>Per batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Edible panel</td><td>$150-250</td><td>Per batch</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Monthly budget</td><td>$2,000-10,000</td><td>Depends on volume</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Mandatory:</strong> All products must test before sale</li>
        <li><strong>⚠️ Failure = Destroy:</strong> Failed tests mean product loss</li>
        <li><strong>💡 Pro-Hack:</strong> Build lab relationships for discounts</li>
        <li><strong>📊 Budget:</strong> Plan $2K-10K/month for testing</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OCP Rules Chapter 5</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-extraction-licensing/">Extraction Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only. Consult qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>